    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, increasing the timeout might just make the requests pile up more. The weird part is that even after we scaled up the `payment-gateway-auth` instances, we're still seeing these random timeouts that don't seem to correlate with CPU or memory spikes. It feels almost... I don't know, totally unpredictable. Like it's just hitting a wall for no reason sometimes. Is there anything else in the logs that looks weird or any other architectural reason why it would act so sporadically?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sporadic timeouts without clear resource spikes could indicate network instability, such as intermittent packet loss, or an issue with connection pooling on the gateway itself. Check the network metrics between your service and the payment gateway for observed latency or dropped connections. Furthermore, review the payment gateway's own logs for rate limiting, connection throttling, or backend queue buildup that might not appear as a standard CPU spike in their infrastructure.",
      "source": "target",
